{{one source|date=July 2010}}
'''Eli Hirsch''' is an American [[philosopher]] and the Charles Goldman Professor of Philosophy at [[Brandeis University]].<ref name=B>[http://www.brandeis.edu/facguide/person.html?emplid=3b8c58f368269c9b2a81bea2caf5cd32e3d4e84a Brandeis University faculty guide], retrieved 2010-06-26.</ref>

He is best known for his work in [[meta-ontology]].  He coined the phrase "[[soft ontology]]" and has authored numerous books such as ''The Concept of Identity'' and ''Dividing Reality.''
Hirsch received a Ph.D. and M.A. from NYU, and a B.A. from CUNY Brooklyn College. He has written 10 published works.<ref name=B/>

