{{Orphan|date=October 2015}}
{{ZenBuddhism}} {{Buddhism}} '''Gyeongbong''' ({{lang-ko|경봉}}, {{zh|鏡峰}} 1892&ndash;1982) was a [[Korea]]n [[Buddhist]] monk, Ordained in 1907 at the age of 15, Master Gyeongbong was born in Milyang, Gyeongnam Province, in 1892. Master Gyeongbong was Abbot of [[Tongdosa|Tongdo Temple]] in Yangsang, one of the most important [[Jogye|Jogye Order]] temples in Korea. At [[Tongdosa|Tongdo Temple]], Master Gyeongbong became famous for the many monks he taught.<ref>Jeongdo (2013). ''Study on Gyeongbong Seonsa''. Unjusa. {{ISBN|9788957463444}}</ref> After turning 90, Master Gyeongbong began to give dharma speeches, which more than one thousand people would regularly attend. In 1982, Master Gyeongbong wrote his last lecture, “Touch the Crossbar at Midnight,” and died.<ref>"The preaching of Buddha: Gyeongbong Seonsa". [http://www.ibulgyo.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=38166/ Bulgyo Sinmun ]</ref>
